The man died while working on the ship on Tuesday afternoon and paramedics say a metal object fell on his head. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating the death of a man on a ship docked at Cape Town Harbour. The man died while working on the ship on Tuesday afternoon. Paramedics say a metal object fell on his head. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana said: "Police are investigating a case of inquest following an incident where a man in his twenties was injured and fatally wounded. Circumstances around the incident are under investigation." (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo)